File: Pieter Doorewaard and Phillip Schutte were found guilty of killing teenager Matlhomola Moshoeu. MUJAHID SAFODIEN / AFP JOHANNESBURG - The Supreme Court of Appeal has overturned the convictions of two men, previously found guilty of the murder of a Coligny teenager. Pieter Doorewaard and Phillip Schutte had maintained their innocence throughout the trial. The two allegedly killed 16-year old Matlhomola Moshoeu, by throwing him out of a moving bakkie in 2017. READ: New appeal for Coligny killers The teenager was accused of stealing sunflower from a farm. Doorewaard and Schutte were sentenced to an effective 18-year and 23-year prison sentence, respectively.